2)Keep officers to a minimum, that way you dont have a ton of people getting invited to the guild and dont know who the hell they are. The people you invite, should be sent on some kind of quest, make them go on a raid with you and show there honor by slaying a gnome or something to that effect, or guard duty for an hour at one of the lifts in kele, also, i like the idea of having officers head of thier class, that way they can take care of the problems the people in that class may have and it doesnt all fall on you (guild leader).<br>
3) there should be no begging in guild chat, the reason is it is annoying as hell! earn yer gear! Also no arguing in guild chat, that can screw yer guild up in a heart beat, if 2 players have an argument take it to tells, if it can not be resolved that way then speak to an officer.<br>
4) Before anyone joins the guild make them get an account with your web page,and encourage them to check it every few days, that way the know whats going on.<br>
<br>
Ummmmm thats all i can think of right now but if i come up with anything else ill let ya know, so that my two copper pieces.<br>
<br>
